SIMPLE: hoodwink
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hoodwink
<hw>Hood"wink</hw> <pr>(h⟦oocr⟧d"w⟦icr⟧⟦nsm⟧k)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hood</ets> + <ets>wink</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
blind by covering the eyes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We will blind and <qex>hoodwink</qex> him.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To cover; to hide.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To deceive by false appearance; to impose
upon.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Hoodwinked</xex> with kindness.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Sir P. Sidney.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hoody</ent>⟦br⟧
